  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the moderate amount of $25,000 and the proactive effort to make partial restitution justify a sentence on the lower end of the sentencing scale. A period of 6 months incarceration is sufficient to address the punitive requirements of the law while acknowledging the rehabilitative potential of a first-time offender.",
  "verdict": 6
